programme.title: Ô la belle vie
programme.desc: Nîmes: of women and Roman heritage From the 1st century AD, Emperor Augustus, adopted son of Julius Caesar, made Nîmes one of the most important Roman colonies in Gaul. programme.desc:

More than enough to encourage Marleau to take a close interest in him.

programme.desc:
Season: 2021

The Pays de Nancy and the Lunévillois

We head for north-eastern France to meet Véronique, using permaculture methods to grow cut-flowers and vegetables. On a farm handed down from generation to generation, Sabine grows cherry plums and distils Lorraine whisky. We explore Jean-Marie Pelt's botanical garden, the Château de Lunéville, Bergamote de Nancy...

Presented by: Guy Martin.

programme.title: Décolonisations, du sang et des larmes
programme.desc:
Part 1: The split (1931-1954)

In the 1930s, when the French colonial empire was at its height, the first demands for independence began to make themselves heard, but France remained deaf to all the protests. Senegal, Indochina, Madagascar, Algeria, Morocco, Côte d'Ivoire... France did everything possible to preserve its colonies. But in vain.

Directed by: David Korn-Brzoza (France, 2019)

programme.title: Sale temps pour la planète
programme.desc: Landes de Gascogne, swept away by the wind The highest and longest dunes in Europe, Europe's largest man-made forest, the second largest department in France by surface area: the Landes de Gascogne seem to accumulate all the superlatives. But the natural balance is fragile, two storms have devastated the forests, floods paralysed the towns, hail destroyed crops... Directed by: Morad Aït-Habbouche (season 13, France, 2019)

programme.title: Sale temps pour la planète
programme.desc: Alps, the climate challenge The Alpine massif is one of the places in France where global warming is being most keenly felt. The glaciers are visibly melting; permafrost is disappearing and increasing risks for climbers and hikers. How much longer will skiing still be possible in the Alps? Directed by: Morad Haït-Habbouche (France, season 13, 2019)
